news.title: Blackstone to buy Preferred Apartment Communities in $5.8 billion deal
news.para: Blackstone Real Estate Income Trust's (BREIT) all-cash offer of $25 per share is nearly 40% higher than Preferred Apartment's stock close on Feb. 9, a day before media reports on the company exploring strategic options including a sale.

news.title: Pune: Broking agency accused of diverting 6.24 crore
news.para: The firm has complained that the manager of the broking agency created a separate account in the name of the realty firm and diverted the money to it without its knowledge.

news.title: Schindler expects China business to contract in 2022 on construction delays
news.para: The Swiss firm expects a "significant" profitability drop of around 20% for the first half of the year, Chief Financial Officer Urs Scheidegger said on a conference call.

news.title: Demand for housing continues to remain robust: Deepak Parekh, Chairman, HDFC
news.para: According to Parekh, the demand for housing continues to be from both first-time homeowners as well as those moving up the property ladder - generally into larger homes or houses in other locations.

news.title: Gujarat: Furniture park may be outside SIPC
news.para: The DPT and ministry of ports, shipping, and waterways were trying to convince timber units to come to the SIPC since 2019 for the park, which was an ambitious project of Prime Minister Narendra Modi.

news.title: Hurdles in land acquisition to delay Patna metro project
news.para: Around 650 people have objected to land acquisition. The district land acquisition officer has listened to their grievances. Some people have even approached the court.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso residents demand arrest of firm's directors
news.para: Handing out a nine-point demand letter to local MLA Rakesh Daultabad, who visited the residents, they demanded an investigation into the entire incident along with the alleged malpractices of the builder under the direct supervision of the Punjab and Haryana High Court.

news.title: Puravankara to invest Rs 1,550 crore to construct 3 million realty project in Kochi
news.para: The company's subsidiary Provident Housing Ltd will develop 3 million square feet in the project, which is spread over 18 acres, named 'Provident Winworth' at Kochi.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board seeks green clearance for IT Park housing project
news.para: Recently, the urban planning and engineering departments of the UT administration had approved the plan to construct 728 flats in around 16.6 acres of land of two pockets at Rs 643 crore.

news.title: Construction waste recovery plant in Kolkata to start operations in April
news.para: The construction waste recovery plant in Rajarhat is nearing completion. According to a Kolkata Municipal Corporation official, the plant is expected to start its operations from April. It will have a capacity to handle 500 tonnes of waste in a day.

news.title: Nagpur civic body panel seeks new rules to approve existing building violations
news.para: For minor violations like excess construction, utilization of margin spaces etc, the civic body had issued notices to many under the Maharashtra Regional and Town Planning (MRTP) Act.

news.title: Chandigarh administration tells slum dwellers to vacate colony no. 4 in two months
news.para: “This colony is illegal and will be demolished within two months. It is hereby ordered to vacate it,” read a notice pasted on the wall of a house in the colony.

news.title: Remove bar to sell sites on freehold, says Chandigarh housing board
news.para: In a letter, the CHB has submitted that 123.79 acres of land had been allotted to CHB on freehold basis at IT Park in August 2006. However, a restriction has been provided in the conveyance deed.

news.title: Call grows for five year structural audits of high-rises in Noida
news.para: A NCF team met Praveen Mishra, the additio-nal CEO of the Noida Authority, on Wednesday to press for their demand of the structural audit in view of several incidents of plasters peeling off highrise buildings in Noida in the recent past.

news.title: Malls start charging full rentals, end concessions
news.para: Unfair to charge pre-Covid rentals as some businesses have not become fully operational, say tenants.
